COPENHAGEN, May 20 (Xinhua) -- At least four people were injured, with one in critical condition, during a random stabbing attack on Friday in Numedal, a river valley 84 km southeast of Norway's capital city of Oslo, local police said. The police received the report around 8:58 a.m. local time (0658 GMT), and the perpetrator was apprehended 10-15 minutes later, Kai Redalen, local fire police chief, told Norwegian national television NRK.  â– 